bert Richter, Martin Rickelt, Michael Symo, Friedrich Teitge, [[Nico Turoff]] and Christine von Tr\u00fcmbach ||\n|-\n| ''[[Leaving Metropolis]]'' || {{Sortname|Brad|Fraser}} || Canada || Comedy, drama || Troy Ruptash, [[Vince Corazza]] (billed as Vincent Corazza), [[Lynda Boyd]], [[Cherilee Taylor]], Thom Allison, Arne MacPherson, Tom Anniko, Paul Stafford, Chris Sigurdson (billed as Christopher Sigurdson), Susan Kelso, Blake Taylor, Kirsten Johnson, John Bluethner and David Brindle || Based on Fraser's play ''Poor Super Man''\n|-\n| ''[[Lis\u00edstrata]]'' || {{Sortname|Francesc|Bellmunt}} || Spain || Comedy || [[Maribel Verd\u00fa]], [[Juan Luis Galiardo]], Javier Gurruchaga, [[Jes\u00fas Bonilla]], Tet\u00e9 Delgado (billed as Tete Delgado), Aitor Mazo, Gl\u00f2ria Cano, Eduardo Antu\u00f1a, Antonio Belart, Cristina Sol\u00e0, Anna Maria Barbany (billed as Anna M\u00aa Barbany), Albert Trifol, [[Sonia Ferrer]] (billed as S\u00f2nia Ferrer), Sergio Pazos and Jos\u00e9 Corbacho || Based on a comic book by [[Ralf K\u00f6nig]], which in turn is loosely based on the play ''[[Lysistrata]]'' by [[Aristophanes]]\n|-\n| ''[[Lovers' Kiss]]'' || [[Ataru Oikawa]] || Japan || Drama, romance || [[Aya Hirayama]], [[Hiroki Narimiya]] || Based on a [[manga]] by [[Akimi Yoshida]]\n|-\n| ''[[Luster (film)|Luster]]'' || {{Sortname|Everett|Lewis}} || United States || Comedy, drama|| [[Justin Herwick]], Shane Powers, [[B. Wyatt]], [[Pamela Gidley]], [[Susannah Melvoin]], [[Willie Garson]], [[Jonah Blechman]], [[Sean Thibodeau]], [[Henriette Mantel]], [[Norman Reedus]] and [[Chris Freeman (musician)|Chris Freeman]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[My Life on Ice]]'' || {{Sortname|Olivier|Ducastel}}, [[Jacques Martineau]] || France || Comedy || [[Jimmy Tavares]], [[Ariane Ascaride]], [[Jonathan Zacca\u00ef]], H\u00e9l\u00e8ne Surg\u00e8re, Lucas Bonnifait, Hanako Bron and [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Gorny]] ||a.k.a. ''Ma vraie vie \u00e0 Rouen''\n|-\n| ''[[Madame Sat\u00e3 (film)|Madame Sat\u00e3]]'' || {{Sortn